id,text
bio_graph_0000135,"Inside a closed nutrient basin, there are 6 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, and F.
the adult population participates in a closed nutrient-exchange structure.

Biologists established the following rules:
- each specie has directed outgoing interactions toward exactly 1 distinct others.
- each specie receives directed input from exactly 2 others.
- no organism interacts with itself.
- no directed interaction is reciprocated.
- the full nutrient network must be strongly connected.

Observed relationships:
- A draws nutrients from B.
- B draws nutrients from C.
- C draws nutrients from D.
- D draws nutrients from A.
- E draws nutrients from C.
- F draws nutrients from E.

Determine whether a valid completion exists. If it does, provide one valid completion. If it does not, identify the contradiction."
bio_graph_0000216,"In a closed microbial suppression experiment, there are 7 strains labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, and G. researchers recorded two directed interaction types: stimulation and suppression. The system obeys the following rules: no entity interacts with itself; for any ordered pair, at most one interaction type may occur; each entity stimulates exactly 3 distinct others; each entity suppresses exactly 1 distinct others; each entity receives exactly 1 incoming activation links; each entity receives exactly 1 incoming inhibition links; no pair of entities may mutually activate one another; if X suppresses Y, then Y stimulates X is forbidden. Observations additionally show that A stimulates B; B stimulates C; C suppresses A. Can the observations be extended to a full valid signaling network? Give a construction if possible, or prove impossibility if not."
bio_graph_0000222,"Inside a sealed microbial signaling chamber, there are 7 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, and G. researchers observed two kinds of directed adult-phase signaling: activation and inhibition. The system obeys the following rules: no entity interacts with itself; for any ordered pair, at most one interaction type may occur; each entity activates exactly 3 distinct others; each entity inhibits exactly 1 distinct others; each entity receives exactly 1 incoming activation links; each entity receives exactly 2 incoming inhibition links; no pair of entities may mutually activate one another; if X inhibits Y, then Y activates X is forbidden. Observations additionally show that A activates B; B activates C; C inhibits A. Determine whether a valid full interaction network exists. If it does, provide one witness. Otherwise, identify the contradiction."
bio_graph_0000203,"Within a lab-designed signaling network, there are 6 proteins labeled A, B, C, D, E, and F.
the system contains both directed activation and directed inhibition effects.

Researchers established the following rules:
- no entity interacts with itself.
- for any ordered pair, at most one interaction type may occur.
- each entity activates exactly 1 distinct others.
- each entity inhibits exactly 1 distinct others.
- each entity receives exactly 1 incoming activation links.
- each entity receives exactly 1 incoming inhibition links.
- no pair of entities may mutually activate one another.
- if X inhibits Y, then Y activates X is forbidden.
- the combined interaction graph must be strongly connected.
- every entity must lie on at least one directed cycle in the combined graph.
- no directed 3-cycle may consist entirely of activation edges.

Observed interactions:
- A inhibits B.
- B activates A.
- A activates C.

Is there a complete interaction system satisfying all rules and observations? If yes, construct one; if no, explain why not."
bio_graph_0000206,"Within a laboratory-grown microbial community, there are 8 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, and H. adult-phase interactions are of two directed kinds: activation and inhibition. The system obeys the following rules: no entity interacts with itself; for any ordered pair, at most one interaction type may occur; each entity activates exactly 2 distinct others; each entity inhibits exactly 1 distinct others; each entity receives exactly 2 incoming activation links; each entity receives exactly 1 incoming inhibition links; no pair of entities may mutually activate one another; if X inhibits Y, then Y activates X is forbidden; the combined interaction graph must be strongly connected; every entity must lie on at least one directed cycle in the combined graph; no directed 3-cycle may consist entirely of activation edges. Observations additionally show that H activates B; D activates F; D inhibits A; C activates D. Can the observations be extended to a full valid signaling network? Give a construction if possible, or prove impossibility if not."
bio_graph_0000220,"Inside a closed regulatory experiment, there are 8 proteins labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, and H.
the system contains both directed activation and directed inhibition effects.

Researchers established the following rules:
- no entity interacts with itself.
- for any ordered pair, at most one interaction type may occur.
- each entity activates exactly 3 distinct others.
- each entity inhibits exactly 1 distinct others.
- each entity receives exactly 1 incoming activation links.
- each entity receives exactly 1 incoming inhibition links.
- no pair of entities may mutually activate one another.
- if X inhibits Y, then Y activates X is forbidden.

Observed interactions:
- A activates B.
- B activates C.
- C inhibits A.

Can the observations be extended to a full valid signaling network? Give a construction if possible, or prove impossibility if not."
bio_graph_0000189,"In a sealed marsh habitat, there are 11 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, and K.
biologists recorded a regular feeding network among the adult species.

Biologists established the following rules:
- each specie preys on exactly 2 distinct others.
- each specie is targeted by exactly 2 others.
- no species preys on itself.
- no two species prey on each other.
- the full ecosystem must be strongly connected.
- every species must lie on at least one directed cycle.
- no directed 3-cycle may appear.

Observed relationships:
- A preys on B.
- B preys on C.
- C preys on A.

Is a full interaction network satisfying all rules possible? If yes, construct one. If no, explain why not."
bio_graph_0000192,"On a remote volcanic island, there are 6 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, and F.
the adult species participate in a stable predation network.

Biologists established the following rules:
- each specie preys on exactly 1 distinct others.
- each specie is targeted by exactly 1 others.
- no species preys on itself.
- no two species prey on each other.
- the full ecosystem must be strongly connected.

Observed relationships:
- B preys on C.
- F preys on A.
- C does not prey on B.

Is a full interaction network satisfying all rules possible? If yes, construct one. If no, explain why not."
bio_graph_0000232,"On a remote volcanic island, there are 5 species labeled A, B, C, D, and E.
adult species form a directed feeding network.

Biologists established the following rules:
- each specie preys on exactly 1 distinct others.
- each specie is targeted by exactly 1 others.
- no species preys on itself.
- no two species prey on each other.
- the full ecosystem must be strongly connected.
- every species must lie on at least one directed cycle.

Observed relationships:
- A preys on B.
- B preys on C.
- C preys on D.
- D preys on E.

Determine whether a valid completion exists. If it does, provide one valid completion. If it does not, identify the contradiction. Also determine whether the completion is unique."
bio_graph_0000187,"Within a closed reef ecosystem, there are 7 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, and G. the mature species interact through recurring predation links. The system obeys the following rules: each specie preys on exactly 1 distinct others; each specie is targeted by exactly 1 others; no species preys on itself; no two species prey on each other; the full ecosystem must be strongly connected; every species must lie on at least one directed cycle; no directed 3-cycle may appear. Field observations additionally record that A preys on B; B preys on C; C preys on A. Determine whether a valid completion exists. If it does, provide one valid completion. If it does not, identify the contradiction."
