bio_graph_0000185,"Within a closed reef ecosystem, there are 9 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, and I. the adult species participate in a stable predation network. The system obeys the following rules: each specie preys on exactly 2 distinct others; each specie is targeted by exactly 2 others; no species preys on itself; no two species prey on each other; the full ecosystem must be strongly connected; every species must lie on at least one directed cycle. Field observations additionally record that B preys on D; I preys on A; B preys on C; E preys on F. Determine whether a valid completion exists. If it does, provide one valid completion. If it does not, identify the contradiction."
